Summary: This section provides guidance on resolving unexpected physics behavior in Godot, including configuration adjustments and checking known engine issues.
When working with a physics engine, you may encounter unexpected results. While many of these issues can be resolved through configuration, some of them are the result of engine bugs. For known issues related to the physics engine, see open physics-related issues on GitHub. Looking through closed issues can also help answer questions related to physics engine behavior.
